    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Crew backed the pipe skate up to free the casing from the girt",
      "Onsite investigation conducted 27-FEB-2014"
    ],
    "summary": "On 21-FEB-2014 at 2110 hours, while pulling 9.875\" casing from the wellbore on the Diamond Ocean Victory, a joint of casing slipped off the pipe skate while still connected to the Top Drive single joint elevators. The hinge pin on the elevators had become hung-up on the derrick girt. As the casing swung back toward the well center, the Injured Person crossed the rig floor beneath the suspended load and was struck in the mid-section, pinned between the casing in the rotary and the suspended joint.",
    "recommendations": [
      "BSEE New Orleans District made no recommendations to the Agency"
    ],
